{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"9":{"eng-name":"Zakat (Kitab Al-Zakat)","ara-name":"كتاب الزكاة"}},"section_detail":{"9":{"hadithnumber_first":1556,"hadithnumber_last":1700,"arabicnumber_first":1556,"arabicnumber_last":1700}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1643,"arabicnumber":1643,"text":"Thawban, the client of the Messenger of Allah (May peace be upon him), reported him as saying :If anyone guarantees me that he will not beg from people, I will guarantee him Paradise. Thawban said : I (will not beg). He never asked anyone for anything","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Isnaad Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":9,"hadith":88},"chapter":{"id":28,"ara-name":"باب كَرَاهِيَةِ الْمَسْأَلَةِ","eng-name":"Disapproval Of Begging","isFirstHadith":false}}]}